Researchers at Iowa State University recorded 300 hunts by chimps in Fongoli, Sénégal . 
  They found female chimps were using tools to capture prey in 60 per cent of the hunts . 
  However, the male chimpanzees tended to capture larger prey with their hands . 
  The chimps are the only animals to regularly hunt for prey with tools . 
  Researchers observed more females using broken sticks to help them capture prey . 
 